) Pedicellus with long setae, more than three times the diameter of segment in males. The lateral tubercles of pronotum cov 
<pageBreakToken pageId="12" pageNumber="63" start="start">ered</pageBreakToken>
with stiff setae. Fore femora with seven spines ventrally and dorsally covered by conspicuous setigerous tubercles.
</paragraph>
